<TEI xmlns="http://www.tei-c.org/ns/1.0" xmlns:frus="http://history.state.gov/frus/ns/1.0"><text><body><div frus:doc-dateTime-max="1916-01-21T07:00:00-05:00" frus:doc-dateTime-min="1916-01-21T07:00:00-05:00" n="196" subtype="historical-document" type="document" xml:id="d196">
                            <note rend="inline" type="source">File No. 763.72/2351</note>
                            <head>
                                <hi rend="italic">The Ambassador in Germany</hi> (<persName corresp="#p_GJW1" type="from"><hi rend="italic">Gerard</hi></persName>) <hi rend="italic">to the <gloss type="to">Secretary of State</gloss>
                                </hi>
                            </head>
                            <opener>
                                <seg rendition="#center">[Telegram]</seg>
                            </opener>
                            <opener>
                                <dateline rendition="#right">
                                    <placeName>
                                        <hi rend="smallcaps">Berlin</hi></placeName>, <date calendar="gregorian" when="1916-01-21T13:00:00+01:00">
                                        <hi rend="italic">January 21, 1916, 1 p. m.</hi>
                                    </date>
                                    <lb/> [<hi rend="italic">Received January 22, 1.15 p.
                                    m.</hi>]</dateline>
                            </opener>
                            <p>3375. It may have escaped your notice but I am utterly without
                                information as to your negotiations on <hi rend="italic">Lusitania</hi> case. If such negotiations are pending I can
                                perhaps be of some assistance from this end, but unless I know what
                                is going on and what you desire to accomplish I can be of little
                                service in this matter. I expect <persName corresp="#p_HEM1">Colonel
                                    House</persName> 25th.</p>
                            <closer>
                                <signed>
                                    <persName corresp="#p_GJW1">
                                        <hi rend="smallcaps">Gerard</hi>
                                    </persName>
                                </signed>
                            </closer>
                        </div>
                        </body></text></TEI>